java.io.Serializable
public class JSimSimulationAlreadyTerminatedException
extends JSimException

The JSimSimulationAlreadyTerminatedException is thrown whenever the user attempts to add a new process into a terminated simulation. Simulation is terminated if there are no more scheduled events or there are no more processes. You should never need to create an instance of this class.

J-Sim version 0.1.0
